data.description: OPEN Floor plan **EXPANSIVE ONE LEVEL LIVING 4 Bedrooms with flexible floor plan ** MODERN DESIGN with COMPLETELY RENOVATED INTERIOR ** Interesting Historical information regarding Southbury train station also previously used as an artist studio. Total Re-DO! Explore a piece of history with all of today's modern updates! ** Hardwood floors ** RENOVATION in 2014-2018 (Roof, Vinyl Siding, Electric, Heating, AC, Plumbing, Hardwood floors, Septic and 25x24 detached garage) ** Front entry gives access to a private suite (could be 2nd primary bedroom suite, an in home office with half bath, family room or IN-LAW/guest suite). French doors to a sweeping great room with sliders to the deck, open to the STUNNING MODERN kitchen with granite, island, tile backsplash, stainless steel appliances. Formal dining room with mahogany bordered HW floors. Main floor Office. Generous size bedrooms including the Primary bedroom with two closets and full bath with walk in tile shower! UPDATED BATHS * Oversized two car detached garage (25x24) newly constructed with high ceilings; DECK overlooks beautiful LEVEL yard, privacy fence and patio; perfect for outdor gatherings and relaxation. Adjacent to Larkin State Bridle Trail (10.3 miles; follows an old railroad trail dating back to the late 1800s). Location and layout is perfect for a professional or business in-home office; ideal for focused work environment!
